30 namespace psy {

32 
33 class ParserTester final : public Tester
34 {
35 public:
36  ParserTester(TestSuite* suite)
37  : Tester(suite)
38  {}
39 
40  static const std::string Name;
41  virtual std::string name() const override { return Name; }
42  virtual void setUp() override;
43  virtual void tearDown() override;
44 
45  void testParser();
46 
47  void parseDeclaration(std::string text, Expectation X = Expectation());
48  void parseExpression(std::string text, Expectation X = Expectation());
49  void parseStatement(std::string text, Expectation X = Expectation());
50  void parse(std::string text,
51  Expectation X = Expectation(),
52  SyntaxTree::SyntaxCategory synCat = SyntaxTree::SyntaxCategory::UNSPECIFIED);
53 
54  using TestFunction = std::pair<std::function<void(ParserTester*)>, const char*>;
55 
56  /*
57  Declarations:
58  + 0000-0099 -> object declarations
59  + 0100-0199 -> object declarations of array and function types
60  + 0200-0279 -> function declarations/definitions
61  + 0280-0299 -> function definitions K&R
62  + 0300-0399 -> array declarations
63  + 0400-0499 -> `struct' and `union' declarations and type specifiers
64  + 0500-0599 -> `enum' declarations and type specifiers
65  + 0600-0649 -> storage class specifiers
66  + 0650-0669 -> `_Static_assert'
67  + 0670-0699 -> GNU: `__extension__'
68  + 0700-0779 -> GNU: `__attribute__'
69  + 0780-0799 -> GNU: `__asm__' (file scope and labels)
70  + 0800-0849 -> brace-enclosed initializaters
71  + 0850-0899 -> designated initializers
72  + 0900-0949 -> GNU: `__typeof__' (w/ ambiguity)
73  + 0950-0999 -> `__Alignas'
74 
75  Expressions:
76  + 1000-1099 -> identifiers, constants, and string-literals
77  + 1100-1199 -> parenthesized expression
78  + 1200-1249 -> generic selection
79  + 1250-1299 -> compound literal
80  + 1300-1349 -> (pre/post) increment and decrement
81  + 1350-1399 -> unary arithmetic
82  + 1400-1449 -> `sizeof'
83  + 1450-1499 -> `_Alignof'
84  + 1500-1549 -> member access
85  + 1550-1599 -> array element access
86  + 1600-1649 -> calls
87  + 1650-1699 -> address-of and indirection
88  + 1700-1749 -> casts (w/ ambiguity)
89  + 1750-1799 -> conditional
90  + 1800-1849 -> binary and sequencing
91  + 1850-1899 -> assignment
92  + 1900-1949 -> GNU: statement-expressions
93  + 1950-1959 -> GNU: `__builtin_va_arg'
94  + 1960-1969 -> GNU: `__builtin_offsetof'
95  + 1970-1979 -> GNU: `__builtin_choose_expr'
96  + 1980-1989 -> GNU: `__FUNCTION__' and `__PRETTY_FUNCTION__'
97  + 1990-1999 -> GNU: `__real__' and `__imag__'
98 
99  Statements:
100  + 2000-2019 -> `goto' and identifier labels
101  + 2020-2099 -> compound statements
102  + 2100-2199 -> expression statements
103  + 2200-2299 -> declaration statements (w/ ambiguity)
104  + 2300-2349 -> `if'
105  + 2350-2399 -> `switch', `case', and `default'
106  + 2400-2449 -> `while'and `do'
107  + 2450-2499 -> `for'
108  + 2500-2549 -> `break', `continue', and `return'
109  + 2550-2599 ->
110  + 2600-2699 -> GNU: `__asm__'
111 
112  Macro translation:
113  + 3000-3009 -> `va_arg'
114  + 3010-3019 -> `offsetof'
115  + 3020-3029 -> `__func__'
116  + 3030-3039 ->
117  + 3040-3099 ->
118  + 3100-3199 ->
119  + 3200-3299 ->
120  + 3300-3399 ->
121  + 3400-3499 ->
122  + 3500-3599 ->
123  */
